# TestRail case titles

When creating or updating TestRail cases:

## Format

1. **Title:** `When <action/condition>, then <expected result>`
2. **`and` is optional** only when it adds clarity
3. **Negative:** start with `[neg]`  
   Example: `[neg] When Cancel is clicked, then unsaved changes are discarded`

## Clarity

4. Short, clear, unambiguous. Title alone must tell what is tested (~8–16 words)
5. Prefer **concrete objects + outcomes** (Draft detail, Order form, Published record)
6. Cut filler (“the user”, “successfully”, “as expected”). Nuance goes in Steps/Expected

## Verb & trigger precision

1. Trigger verb = real AC/UI event (`created`, `opened`, `published`), not a nearby step (`saved` ≠ `created` unless testing Save)
2. Subject = what the tester looks at (e.g. Draft editor)
3. Outcome = observable result
4. If unclear, draft 1 title in chat then ACC/EDIT before TestRail write

| Bad | Good |
|-----|------|
| When a New Item is **saved**, then the Draft editor contains default content | When a New Item is **created**, then the Draft editor contains default content |
| When the user does something and then things update correctly | When Draft content is saved, then content persists |
| Negative: empty selection behavior | `[neg] When Spec is saved with no selection, then reopen shows no selection` |

## Fields & template

8. Always fill **Preconditions**, **Steps**, and **Expected Result**
9. Prefer TestRail **Text** template (`templateId: 1`)
